You can run a command on all windows in the current collection with :windo<br><br>

To do a find and replace on the current set of windows do:<br>
:windo %s/foo/bar<br>
This will replace foo with bar in each file.<br><br>
:windo %s/;$// <br>
This will remove semicolons at the end of lines in javascript.<br><br>
Alternatively (not pictured in the above gif) you can run a macro on each
open by using :windo execute "normal @a" | update - to run macro @ and save after file change.

